---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}(trimmed and sliced) (skip if your
mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and remove strings from @Sugar Snap Peas{4%ounce}(trimmed and strings removed). Trim and thinly slice
@Scallions{2%unit}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @Lo Mein Noodles{4.5%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Drain and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and
slightly crispy, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add snap peas, @Shredded Carrots{4%ounce}, scallion whites, and another drizzle
of oil. Cook, stirring, until veggies are just tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a small #bowl{} (medium bowl for 4 servings), combine
@Sesame Oil{1%tablespoon}, @Soy Sauce{1%ounce}, @Pho Stock Concentrate{1%unit},
half the @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}, and ¼ cup water (½ cup for 4).

Stir drained noodles and sesame sauce into pan with veggies. Simmer, stirring
occasionally, until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes} (3-4 minutes for 4 servings).
Taste and season lightly with pepper if desired.

Divide sesame mushroom lo mein between bowls. Garnish with scallion greens
and drizzle with remaining Sriracha to taste. Serve.